com.nobigsoftware.dfalex

Interface DfaAmbiguityResolver<MATCHRESULT>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.util.function.Function<java.util.Set<MATCHRESULT>,MATCHRESULT>, java.io.Serializable

    public interface DfaAmbiguityResolver<MATCHRESULT>
extends java.io.Serializable, java.util.function.Function<java.util.Set<MATCHRESULT>,MATCHRESULT>
    Implementations of this interface are used to resolve ambiguities in DfaBuilder.

    When it's possible for a single string to match patterns that produce different results, the ambiguity resolve is called to determine what the result should be.

    The implementation can throw a DfaAmbiguityException in this case, or can combine the multiple result objects into a single object if its type (e.g., EnumSet) permits.
